         <entryFree xml:id="k000132" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000132-3" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt" source="#biblk000132-1"
               >jiejianbanzhang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000132-1" xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-2">截間版帳</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000132-2" xml:lang="zh-Hans" source="#biblk000132-3">截间版帐</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000132-6" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin" source="#biblk000132-1"
               >jiéjiānbǎnzhàng</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000132-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin" source="#biblk000132-4">jiejian
               banzhang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000132-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">chieh-chien-pan-chang</term>
            <note type="Note (brief)">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000132-2">Scholars generally agree that jiejian
                  banzhang 截間版帳 is a room dividing partition, and some scholars believe that it is a
                  partition specifically running perpendicular to the main roof ridge. The term is
                  only found in Yingzao fashi 營造法式 as a type of nonstructural carpentry (xiaomuzuo
                  小木作). According to the description in Yingzao fashi, jiejian banzhang is six to
                  ten feet high and is composed of boards (ban 版) and covering strips (yatouhufeng
                  牙頭護縫), which can be used on both sides of board. These components are fixed by a
                  board casing (nanzi 難子) between the columns. If the jiejian banzhang is more than
                  seven feet high, column-top-ties (e’fu 額栿) along with ,posts (tuanzhu 摶柱), and a
                  waist bar (yaochuan 腰串) should be added to the framework. If its width is wider
                  than usual, a bay muntin (qianzhu 槏柱) should also be added. The term jiejian
                  banzhang is related to the use of fabric partitioning within interior decoration
                  before the Song Dynasty. The use of word zhang 帳 in the term seems to indicate the
                  relationship between wooden and fabric room partitions. Among all the xiaomuzuo
                  non structural carpentry types in the Yingzao fashi that include the word zhang,
                  jiejian banzhang is the only one that is a vertical plane partition, and it is
                  thus different from other types, such as Ffo-Ddao zhang 佛道賬, etc.,which areis
                  enclosed like a miniaturesmall building.</p><p xml:lang="en"
                  source="#biblk000132-5"> The Han dynasty text Shiming 釋名, by Liu Xi 劉熙 explains
                  that zhang is covering a bed which was shaped like a dou 鬥, (an ancient rice
                  measuring container possessing revered status) turned upside-down (fudou 覆鬥)
                  .“帳，張也，張施於牀上也，小帳如鬥形，如覆鬥也。” Here, the meaning of zhang is clear: it is similar to
                  other types such as Fo-Dao zhang, which are enclosed, have their own roofs, and
                  provide sheltered space for sculpture or other objects. From the Tang Dynasty
                  onwards zhang was known to have multiple meanings. In addition to an enclosed
                  structure, another meaning of “zhang” was a type of vertical fabric partition,
                  similar to wei 帷. </p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-6">
                  截間版帳，學者們一般認爲它是以木制作的室內隔斷（如梁思成，2001：180），有些則認爲特指進深方向的隔斷（如趙琳，2005：102）。</p><p
                  xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-2"
                  >這一術語在古代文獻中，僅見於宋《營造法式》（李誡，2009：卷六：6a）。</p><p xml:lang="zh-Hant"
                  source="#biblk000132-7"
                  >根據《營造法式》的定義，它由木版、內外並施的牙頭、護縫構成，並用難子固定於柱間，高度六至十尺。如果它的高度達七尺以上，則需增加額栿、槫柱及腰串作為框架。如果它的寬度（進深）較一般廣，則需增立槏柱。
                  有三位學者對截間版帳進行過復原。（梁思成，2001：180；竹島卓一, 1997：234-241; 潘谷西，2005：121）</p><p
                  xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-8">
                  截間版帳這一術語體現出宋代室內裝修中殘留的早期的室內織物分隔的影響。“帳”字的使用暗示這一以木制作的室内隔断與織物的關系。（張十慶 2001:70-71；潘谷西
                  2005：120-122；趙琳 2005：102）</p><p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-5">此外，在《營造法式》所有以“帳”命名的小木作中，截間版帳是惟一一個垂直的面狀隔斷，有別於自身呈圍合狀，有頂而且具有內部空間的各類帳，如佛道帳等。從歷史文獻推斷，“帳”本意為自身围合、内部带有空间的織物構造（釋名8卷、釋名卷第六、明嘉靖翻宋本、（漢）劉熙撰、44b
                     ）；</p><p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-9">表示垂直隔斷的字為“帷”（儀禮疏50卷、儀禮䟽卷第十九：3a、上海涵芬樓景印汪閬原覆宋刊本（漢）鄭玄注（唐）賈公彦疏）。</p><p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-10">很可能至唐，“帳”已有與“帷”同為一意的情況：唐·李善等註的《文選》：“羅帳，羅帷也。”（六臣注文選60卷、卷三十一：4b、景上海涵芬樓藏宋刊本、（南北朝）蕭統編（唐）李善等注）</p><p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000132-11">在梁·顧野王撰，宋·陸彭年重修的《玉篇》中對帳釋義：“帷也，張也，幬也。”（玉篇30卷、卷二十八：2a、四庫全書本、（梁）顧野王撰
                  （宋）陸彭年重修），即“帳”可兼具垂直面狀隔斷與圍合的兩層含義。（Bai Ying白穎，Wang Lijia王麗佳）</p>
            </note>
